claim.claim-text:
1. A method of providing a portfolio by combining a plurality of financial instruments for a prefixed operating period, wherein said method comprises: 
a setting step of systematically setting up beforehand a plurality of fluctuation scenarios of market prices related to the instruments; 
a simulation step of reducing a set of portfolios to be sought by making profit and loss simulation in the future for each one of the plurality o fluctuation scenarios, by using a first parameter representing the fluctuation scenarios and a second parameter representing characteristics of market; 
an optimizing step of configuring the optimum portfolio out of the set of portfolios which have been reduced in the preceding step; and 
a providing step of providing the optimum portfolio together with simulation results on the whole or a part of the fluctuation scenarios.
